WEBVTT

00:29.826 --> 00:31.808
Hello, welcome to God Day.

00:32.589 --> 00:35.692
I'm Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church.

00:36.773 --> 00:44.560
And today I just want to look at one of the big themes, one of the big questions in the area of Bible prophecy.

00:45.541 --> 00:58.674
And this is the question that if you look at the Old Testament prophecies about the coming Messiah, many of them predict that when the Messiah will come,

00:59.522 --> 01:03.827
And he will establish a kingdom of peace on the earth.

01:03.987 --> 01:16.261
And there are prophecies that talk about a universal peace on the earth that they will, all nations will lay down their weapons, they'll turn their weapons into pruning hooks, as it were.

01:16.741 --> 01:24.850
There will be universal peace and prosperity that the Messiah will reign on earth for, you know.

01:26.562 --> 01:31.086
Then, of course, as Christians, we believe that Jesus is the Messiah.

01:32.087 --> 01:44.700
And so this is the question, why didn't Jesus establish his messianic kingdom in fulfillment of all the Bible prophets like Isaiah and Jeremiah and Ezekiel and so on?

01:45.280 --> 01:55.090
Why didn't he establish his kingdom once he had obtained our salvation through the cross and rose from the dead and established the new covenant

01:55.522 --> 02:01.129
Once he had done his work of salvation, why didn't he just go ahead and establish his kingdom?

02:02.611 --> 02:10.501
Why did the church, because after all he told his disciples all authority in heaven and earth has been given to me.

02:11.342 --> 02:21.494
So in his resurrection and ascension he received all the authority to be that king, but instead the church age has taken place.

02:22.475 --> 02:24.658
And why?

02:25.186 --> 02:32.656
And does that mean that that prophesied, promised messianic kingdom will never happen?

02:36.361 --> 02:49.760
To understand what's going on here, it is necessary to look at, as it were, the transition from the old to the new, from the old covenant, the Old Testament to the new.

02:50.861 --> 02:54.546
There's a transition period.

02:54.722 --> 02:57.245
if there's an answer to that question.

02:57.886 --> 03:02.391
As to why the church age came in rather than the messianic kingdom.

03:03.092 --> 03:08.958
It's got to be found in that transition time and that is the time described in the gospels.

03:09.599 --> 03:13.043
Or I would say the ministries of John the Baptist and Jesus Christ.

03:14.445 --> 03:16.727
The answer has to be there.

03:18.429 --> 03:22.674
If you like, we could put it like this, prophecy is like a big jigsaw puzzle.

03:22.786 --> 03:24.968
All right, there's all kinds of pieces all over the Bible.

03:26.210 --> 03:30.434
When you put a jigsaw puzzle up, you put up the framework, which are the main principles.

03:31.515 --> 03:35.279
But another way of thinking of it is there are two halves to the puzzle.

03:35.860 --> 03:40.064
You know, on the one side is all the Old Testament prophecies.

03:41.005 --> 03:49.234
And on the other side is actually what happened when the Messiah came and brought in the church age and they don't seem to fit together.

03:49.506 --> 03:53.492
How can we fit everything together and understand it as a whole?

03:54.514 --> 03:59.763
And why did Jesus establish the church age?

03:59.803 --> 04:09.919
Well, again, we need to understand the join between the Old and the New Testament, which is, again, the ministries of John the Baptist and Jesus.

04:10.300 --> 04:11.522
The answer will be there.

04:12.183 --> 04:14.066
Now, there are two possible answers.

04:14.530 --> 04:18.434
And most of the church world has gone with the wrong answer, in my opinion.

04:19.435 --> 04:20.776
It's not just an opinion.

04:20.856 --> 04:35.652
It's basically, if you take the Bible literally, that means according to its plain meaning, the mantra I use is, if the plain sense makes sense, seek no other sense.

04:37.373 --> 04:39.616
Not the mantra, but the saying that I would use.

04:41.157 --> 04:41.938
In other words,

04:42.114 --> 04:45.079
we should read the whole Bible according to its plain meaning.

04:45.099 --> 04:47.763
That's the only way to truly be submitted to the Bible.

04:48.624 --> 05:05.129
But one solution which I disagree with is to be to say that we need to not take the Old Testament prophets literally, when they describe this kingdom on earth of God, we need to spiritualize Bible prophecy.

05:05.810 --> 05:10.738
In other words, I would say twist the original meaning

05:11.010 --> 05:13.753
in order to make it fit with the church.

05:14.053 --> 05:18.859
And so they would say, well, the church is the fulfillment of these prophecies.

05:18.919 --> 05:23.664
Yes, it prophesies that even nature will be at peace.

05:23.724 --> 05:25.646
The lion will lie down with the lamb.

05:26.207 --> 05:32.995
And so we need to, that is still not happened, literally, but let's spiritualize it.

05:33.035 --> 05:39.442
Let's say that the lion, the aggressive type people in the church will get on with the lambs.

05:39.778 --> 05:43.243
the gentle lamb type of people in the church.

05:43.303 --> 05:52.357
And so you spiritualize it and then you say, oh, well, all those prophecies, once you understand them spiritually, they're fulfilled in the church.

05:52.777 --> 06:05.076
And therefore, there will be no kingdom, Messianic kingdom, with the Messiah reigning on earth from Jerusalem, that will not literally happen.

06:05.136 --> 06:09.202
And sadly, from about the fourth century, the main

06:09.378 --> 06:22.732
part of the church has bought into that explanation and it involves a rejection of the Bible as the literal interpretation of the Bible.

06:23.313 --> 06:38.930
I reject that out of hand because I have to believe that the Bible means what it says and you need to interpret it according to how the original hearers would have understood it and they would have understood and the Jews still

06:39.074 --> 06:45.821
would have understood of Jesus' time that the Messiah will establish his kingdom and it will be centered on Israel.

06:46.522 --> 06:48.124
Israel will be the chief nation.

06:48.244 --> 06:57.034
That's why Jesus returns to Jerusalem, not some other city, because he is coming as the king to reign over the earth from Jerusalem.

06:57.094 --> 07:01.779
And Revelation 20 says that he will reign for a thousand years on earth.

07:03.141 --> 07:04.963
And I believe that that is true.

07:05.303 --> 07:08.146
So how can we understand it then

07:09.186 --> 07:12.290
What happened was different to what was prophesied.

07:13.551 --> 07:15.113
The church age was established.

07:15.473 --> 07:19.959
Does that mean that this prophesied kingdom will not be established?

07:20.739 --> 07:31.472
The alternative, which is the title of this message really, is that this messianic kingdom was postponed for 2,000 years.

07:32.153 --> 07:36.658
Because Israel rejected the offer of the kingdom,

07:37.378 --> 07:44.749
God postponed the kingdom for two thousand years and in the meantime he brought in the church age.

07:45.130 --> 08:06.802
God cut off Israel as his anointed representatives and grafted the church into the olive tree which is the you know represents the gods anointed representative in the earth and for a time period we are in the church age but eventually

08:06.978 --> 08:16.413
As Romans 11 says, God will cut off the Gentiles from that place and bring Israel back into her position.

08:17.215 --> 08:25.729
As God's anointed representatives and God will again bring the kingdom forth through Israel.

08:26.630 --> 08:29.976
And so this kingdom is yet to come in the future.

08:30.116 --> 08:33.842
All history is heading towards the millennium.

08:34.242 --> 08:36.004
the kingdom of God on earth.

08:36.044 --> 08:43.574
When God will be glorified more than any other time in history and it will be the best time on the earth.

08:43.614 --> 08:45.296
It will be the climax of history.

08:45.977 --> 08:58.572
And the church ignores it because we're too busy thinking about the church age and we don't realize that there is greater things yet yet to come on the earth.

08:59.033 --> 09:03.378
And we will rule and reign with Christ during that thousand years.

09:03.810 --> 09:06.733
And this is a very big part of Scripture.

09:08.395 --> 09:13.179
So that's kind of like the big picture.

09:13.259 --> 09:14.841
The kingdom was postponed.

09:14.861 --> 09:22.548
Now, we have a picture of that in the Bible because God brought Israel, God saved Israel at the Exodus.

09:23.529 --> 09:32.338
And she spent about a year at Mount Sinai, and then God's plan A was that Israel would then go and possess her promised land.

09:32.578 --> 09:33.979
And that's a picture of the kingdom.

09:35.201 --> 09:42.868
Once God had prepared Israel spiritually, she would then go and possess her promised land by faith.

09:43.489 --> 09:57.442
But because Israel was in unbelief and rejected Moses' leadership as it were, then she was not allowed to possess her promised land.

09:58.183 --> 10:01.586
And she had to wander in the wilderness for 40 years.

10:01.698 --> 10:05.862
until a later generation under Joshua possessed the promised land.

10:05.922 --> 10:13.869
And in the same way, Jesus, the prophet like unto Moses, he offered Israel the kingdom.

10:14.710 --> 10:22.698
But because they rejected, because of their unbelief, they could not possess their promised kingdom at that time.

10:23.398 --> 10:31.506
And so they came under judgment instead, and they had to wonder in the wilderness of the nations for let's say 40 jubilis.

10:32.162 --> 10:35.467
But there will be Jesus.

10:35.968 --> 10:41.436
The greater than Joshua will return and bring Israel into her promised kingdom.

10:41.557 --> 10:43.620
So that's what's going on.

10:43.680 --> 10:46.544
This kingdom is, delay is not denial.

10:47.546 --> 10:52.053
This kingdom was postponed and the church age came in instead.

10:53.716 --> 10:57.842
But God will still fulfill his promises.

10:58.018 --> 11:02.084
and his purposes, and he will establish his kingdom on earth.

11:02.745 --> 11:03.306
Praise God.

11:03.386 --> 11:08.193
So let's see this in the ministry of John and Jesus.

11:08.233 --> 11:17.067
The major theme in the Gospels is Israel is offered the kingdom, but Israel rejects the kingdom.

11:17.567 --> 11:27.282
And as a result, that generation doesn't receive the kingdom and instead comes under judgment.

11:27.522 --> 11:40.601
Jesus came to suffer and die for our sins and it was also promised that the Messiah would reign over a kingdom of glory.

11:41.343 --> 11:57.106
And the special thing about John the Baptist and of course Jesus is they were not just prophets before the cross, they were before, they were operating under the old covenant

11:58.594 --> 12:02.358
But they weren't just prophets like previous prophets.

12:02.799 --> 12:05.622
They were actually the fulfillment of prophecy.

12:06.342 --> 12:12.669
They were the ones coming in to bring in the new dispensation, the new covenant.

12:13.310 --> 12:19.296
And so they have a very special place in the scheme of things.

12:19.496 --> 12:24.682
That's why Jesus said of John the Baptist in Matthew 11 verse 9 to 11.

12:24.722 --> 12:28.466
He said, a prophet, yes, I say to you, and more than a prophet,

12:28.834 --> 12:29.114
Why?

12:29.194 --> 12:31.777
Because he's the fulfillment of prophecy.

12:32.378 --> 12:39.285
This is he of whom it's written, behold, I send my messenger before your face who will prepare your way before you.

12:39.846 --> 12:40.907
That's Malachi 3.1.

12:41.388 --> 12:48.215
So John the Baptist was the fulfillment of prophecy, Malachi 3.1, the forerunner of the Messiah.

12:48.235 --> 12:58.226
And then it says that John the Baptist was the greatest of all the prophets because he was the fulfillment of prophecy.

13:00.098 --> 13:05.566
He said in another place in verse 13 that all the prophets prophesied unto John.

13:06.768 --> 13:24.995
And so John the Baptist ministry was very important because a new phase of the kingdom came in that they prophesied unto John, but John was the one who was actually came to bring in the kingdom by preparing the way for Christ, who is the king.

13:25.055 --> 13:27.378
And so

13:28.610 --> 13:41.524
When we look at the ministry of John and Jesus, we see again and again that, for instance, in Matthew 3, it says that John came preaching, repent, believe the gospel for the kingdom is at hand.

13:42.405 --> 13:49.072
And Jesus began to preach in Matthew 4, 17, repent for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

13:49.873 --> 13:57.842
Matthew 10, 7, Jesus told his disciples, he said, as you go preach, saying the kingdom of heaven,

13:57.986 --> 13:58.687
is at hand.

13:59.408 --> 14:12.667
And Mark 1, 14 and 15, Jesus came to Galilee preaching the gospel of the Kingdom of God, saying the time is fulfilled and the Kingdom of God is at hand, repent and believe the gospel.

14:13.408 --> 14:20.998
Now, we, you know, after 2000 years of church history, we don't get the fullness of what was going on here.

14:21.900 --> 14:26.386
We have rightly take this individualistically

14:26.626 --> 14:28.649
You know, that this is the gospel.

14:29.370 --> 14:39.163
You know, I think of Romans 14, 17, which says, the kingdom of God is righteousness, peace and joy in the Holy Spirit, you see?

14:39.524 --> 14:43.550
So when the preaching of the gospel is saying, the kingdom is at hand.

14:43.970 --> 14:46.333
In other words, righteousness is at hand.

14:46.373 --> 14:49.017
You can receive the righteousness of Jesus.

14:49.638 --> 14:52.562
You can receive peace with God.

14:52.642 --> 14:54.865
You know, you can receive forgiveness of sins.

14:55.306 --> 14:56.707
It's available to you.

14:56.808 --> 15:00.993
Jesus has paid the price and you can just reach out and receive.

15:01.113 --> 15:06.641
Believe the gospel and receive your salvation and come into the kingdom of God.

15:07.262 --> 15:14.471
And so we would rightly understand this as Jesus preaching to individuals saying the kingdom of God is at hand.

15:14.491 --> 15:20.339
If you repent and believe, then you come into God's kingdom.

15:20.359 --> 15:22.642
But the Jews would have understood.

15:23.170 --> 15:33.766
that the Messiah, when he comes, he is coming to bring in the messianic kingdom, to establish his kingdom through Israel.

15:34.747 --> 15:40.396
And Jesus was not just speaking to individuals, he was preaching to the nation of Israel.

15:40.837 --> 15:43.020
He was saying, I am the Messiah.

15:43.661 --> 15:47.146
I am ready to bring in the kingdom that was promised.

15:48.168 --> 15:52.434
And if you will repent and believe in me as the Messiah,

15:52.610 --> 15:54.793
you can enter into the kingdom.

15:55.755 --> 16:06.732
And particularly as a nation, if you receive me as your Messiah, then the kingdom will be established.

16:06.752 --> 16:08.154
The kingdom of God is at hand.

16:08.534 --> 16:16.507
They would have understood that as the prophesied kingdom that all the prophets spoke about, this messianic kingdom.

16:17.107 --> 16:21.394
And so they would have understood that Jesus was offering the nation.

16:22.498 --> 16:27.525
that generation of Israel, the Messianic Kingdom.

16:28.546 --> 16:43.447
And had they accepted him, then, after his death and resurrection, within a year, he would have established that promised kingdom on the earth.

16:44.468 --> 16:51.858
The only reason he couldn't do that was, of course, the leaders of Israel had rejected him.

16:52.514 --> 17:02.007
And so that's why you see this action in the Bible that Jesus is as it were declaring through his message and through his miracles.

17:02.127 --> 17:11.159
He was declaring that he is the Messiah and he was forcing the leadership of the nation and the people to make up their mind one way or the other.

17:11.239 --> 17:14.083
Are they going to accept him or are they going to reject him?

17:14.844 --> 17:22.034
Because that was the decisive issue and increasingly as his ministry went on,

17:22.754 --> 17:26.058
they increasingly rejected him.

17:27.139 --> 17:32.626
And this offer of the kingdom came to a head at the triumphal entry.

17:33.187 --> 17:38.814
That was when he was officially offering himself to Israel as her king.

17:39.334 --> 17:43.139
Zachariah 9-9 was the prophecy he was fulfilling.

17:43.540 --> 17:46.623
Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion.

17:46.643 --> 17:49.507
Shout, O daughter of Jerusalem.

17:49.987 --> 17:52.050
Your king, the king of Israel.

17:52.578 --> 17:53.479
is coming to you.

17:53.920 --> 18:01.269
He is just and having salvation, lowly and riding on a donkey, a cult, the fall of a donkey.

18:02.151 --> 18:09.941
And so Matthew 21 quotes that verse and says, Jesus came to fulfill that.

18:11.002 --> 18:20.114
And so by riding into Jerusalem, according to this prophecy, Jesus was claiming to be their true king.

18:20.514 --> 18:25.560
And he came in on the donkey rather than the war horse because he was not forcing himself on them.

18:26.621 --> 18:32.527
He was offering himself in humility for them to accept or reject him.

18:33.809 --> 18:42.778
And so he was offering himself to them as the king and he was offering the kingdom to them.

18:43.659 --> 18:49.746
And we can see from the reaction of the crowds that they understood and the people

18:50.050 --> 18:52.112
Many of them welcomed what he was doing.

18:53.033 --> 19:02.402
We read in Mark 11, 9 and 10, those who went before and those who followed cried out saying, Hosanna, that means save now, save now.

19:03.483 --> 19:05.105
They were trucked believing in him.

19:05.906 --> 19:08.248
Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord.

19:08.769 --> 19:12.653
That's the official messianic greeting to welcome the Messiah.

19:12.873 --> 19:16.256
They were doing their best to say yes to the Messiah.

19:17.217 --> 19:18.098
And notice this,

19:18.178 --> 19:22.282
Blessed is the kingdom of our Father David that comes in the name of the Lord.

19:22.642 --> 19:33.233
They understood that he was offering the kingdom, the Davidic kingdom, the earthly kingdom where the Messiah will reign on the throne of David in Jerusalem.

19:33.253 --> 19:37.997
Blessed is the kingdom promised to David, our Father David, that is coming.

19:38.518 --> 19:43.783
They understood that the king was coming to them and his kingdom was coming to them in the name of the Lord.

19:44.023 --> 19:45.284
Who's Anna in the highest?

19:46.125 --> 19:46.866
And so

19:47.042 --> 19:57.293
That is a clear sign that they understood that he was presenting himself to them as their king and he was ready to establish the kingdom.

19:58.234 --> 20:06.963
And, you know, sadly, of course, at the same time, the leaders of Israel were rejecting him.

20:08.986 --> 20:13.010
We see that in Luke 19, 39, it says, some of the Pharisees

20:13.090 --> 20:16.775
call to him from the crowd saying, teacher, rebuke your disciples.

20:17.156 --> 20:22.544
But he answered saying, I tell you, if these should keep silent, the stones would immediately cry out.

20:22.664 --> 20:31.918
So clearly, they were criticizing the crowds and the followers of Jesus, proclaiming him as king.

20:34.982 --> 20:39.609
But Jesus endorsed, he confirmed his messianic claims.

20:40.430 --> 20:42.994
And he said that they're absolutely correct.

20:43.522 --> 20:51.092
and he is confirming, but nevertheless it seems that the leaders were rejecting him.

20:51.593 --> 21:01.206
And that's why Luke 19 describes this and he describes Jesus' response because he knew the response of the leaders.

21:02.027 --> 21:03.810
And he said these words.

21:03.930 --> 21:08.256
It says, as he drew near, he saw the city and wept over it.

21:08.356 --> 21:12.722
And if you go to Jerusalem, there's a church about halfway down where

21:13.058 --> 21:22.373
that is probably where this took place because there's a particularly good view of Jerusalem from this place on the halfway down the Mount of Olives.

21:23.755 --> 21:27.902
The church is called Dominus Flavitt, which means our Lord wept.

21:28.363 --> 21:40.402
And he wept over Jerusalem saying, if you had known even you, especially in this your day, in other words, this was the day when they should have received them as the Messiah.

21:41.538 --> 21:51.732
If you would have known the things that made for your peace, in other words, had they accepted him, they would have come into peace under his leadership.

21:52.613 --> 21:54.416
But now they are hidden from your eyes.

21:54.496 --> 22:04.129
For days will come upon you when your enemies will build an embankment around you and surround you and close you in on every side and level you and your children within you to the ground.

22:04.529 --> 22:10.898
And they will not leave in you one stone upon another because you did not know the time of your visitation.

22:11.330 --> 22:17.780
This was the special time when he presented himself to Israel as the king, offering to set up the kingdom.

22:18.080 --> 22:21.405
But because they rejected him, they wouldn't have the blessing of peace.

22:22.106 --> 22:25.792
But rather, they would come under the judgment.

22:26.894 --> 22:37.190
And so this was confirmed a few days later when he addressed the leaders of Israel in a great judgment talk in Matthew 23.

22:37.230 --> 22:40.114
And he kind of concludes like this in verse

22:40.258 --> 22:55.555
37 to 39, he said, oh, Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the one who kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to her, how often I wanted to gather your children together as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings, but you were not willing.

22:56.116 --> 23:03.004
In other words, he says, I wanted to bring you under my authority, under my protection, under my blessing.

23:03.424 --> 23:08.690
In other words, they could have come, accepted him,

23:08.770 --> 23:14.697
And he would have established his kingdom on earth with Israel as the chief and most blessed nation.

23:15.218 --> 23:17.361
But he says, but you were not willing.

23:18.182 --> 23:19.543
But Israel rejected him.

23:20.445 --> 23:23.769
See, it says your house is left to you, desolate there.

23:23.789 --> 23:27.433
He's predicting the destruction of the temple and the city.

23:27.994 --> 23:33.982
And he says, for I say to you, you will not see me anymore until not forever.

23:34.382 --> 23:37.586
He won't be gone forever, but he's going to go back to heaven.

23:37.954 --> 23:39.336
and they will not see him.

23:40.397 --> 23:46.184
Until you, you, leaders of Israel, say, bless it is he who comes in the name of the Lord.

23:47.105 --> 24:04.867
Then the leaders of Israel in a future time will actually repent of their rejection of Christ and they will say to Jesus, come, we welcome you to come and save us and be our King.

24:05.668 --> 24:07.090
And that will be the cue

24:07.618 --> 24:10.922
for Jesus to return in power and glory.

24:11.362 --> 24:14.205
And then he will establish his kingdom on earth.

24:14.946 --> 24:19.992
So the kingdom has been delayed because of Israel's rejection of the Messiah.

24:20.452 --> 24:29.282
Israel has come under divine discipline and Israel has been cut off from being God's representative during this age.

24:31.364 --> 24:36.690
But it will not be forever because in Romans 11, 25 and 26 it says,

24:36.930 --> 24:49.042
Blindness in part has come upon the Jews, the Israel, until, not forever, but until, the fullness of the Gentiles has come in.

24:49.842 --> 24:58.270
So once the fullness of the harvest of the church ages come in at the rapture, then it says, all Israel will be saved.

24:58.310 --> 25:06.418
In the tribulation, God will bring all Israel to salvation when they will call on Jesus and he will return

25:06.722 --> 25:11.489
to save his electination at the Second Coming of Christ.

25:11.569 --> 25:14.574
And then he will restore the kingdom to Israel.

25:14.874 --> 25:18.180
He will establish his kingdom on earth from Jerusalem.

25:19.281 --> 25:19.882
Praise God.

25:20.102 --> 25:22.887
And he will bring that about.

25:23.347 --> 25:23.968
Hallelujah.

25:24.409 --> 25:27.374
So this is the big picture of Bible prophecy.

25:27.654 --> 25:32.882
Hopefully it helps you to see the overall scheme of things.

25:32.994 --> 25:49.152
God has not finished with Israel, but she is under discipline, but God has brought her back to the Lord to the land in unbelief, but this is a stage of preparation for Israel to actually come back to the Lord.

25:49.832 --> 25:54.177
And she will turn to God even in great tribulation and affliction.

25:54.658 --> 26:02.226
She will turn back and realize Jesus is her Messiah and she will welcome him and he will return.

26:02.370 --> 26:03.711
and establish His Kingdom.

26:03.752 --> 26:08.397
So the Kingdom is not denied by God, but the Kingdom is postponed.

26:09.177 --> 26:16.686
The Kingdom promised to Israel, the Davidic Kingdom, the Messianic Kingdom, the Millennium will be established.

26:17.046 --> 26:23.053
Jesus said in another place, again the context being the leaders of Israel rejecting Him.

26:23.874 --> 26:31.442
Matthew 21.43 it says, the Kingdom of God will be taken from you and given to a nation or a generation

26:31.970 --> 26:33.152
bearing the fruits of it.

26:33.793 --> 26:39.001
So he says, that generation of Israel missed their opportunity to possess the kingdom.

26:39.722 --> 26:51.680
It will be taken from them and it will be given to a future generation of Israel who will bear fruit, who will believe in the Messiah and God will establish the kingdom through Israel.

26:52.200 --> 27:01.234
That is why in Acts 1, 6, when Jesus appeared risen from the dead to his disciples, they asked him, Lord, will you at this time

27:02.082 --> 27:09.512
restore the kingdom to Israel, and that's the kingdom we're talking about.

27:09.592 --> 27:14.199
